# Prisma ORM Rules

## Positive Directives

- Use the singleton Prisma client from `@/lib/prisma` - never instantiate `new PrismaClient()` elsewhere
- Always include `@@index` annotations on foreign key columns for query performance
- Use `onDelete: Cascade` on relations where child records should be removed with the parent (e.g., TicketTiers when an Event is deleted)
- Store monetary values as `Int` (cents), not `Float`
- Use `@db.Text` for long-form content fields (e.g., Event description)
- Always use transactions (`prisma.$transaction`) when creating related records atomically
- Run `npx prisma migrate dev` after every schema change
- Run `npx prisma generate` after pulling schema updates

## Negative Rules

- NEVER use `Float` for monetary values
- NEVER query the database from client components - always use Server Components or Server Actions
- NEVER use raw SQL unless Prisma query builder cannot express the query
- NEVER skip adding indexes on columns used in WHERE or JOIN clauses
- NEVER delete or rename migration files manually

## Verification Steps

- Run `npx prisma validate` to check schema correctness
- Run `npx prisma migrate dev --name <descriptive_name>` to verify migrations apply cleanly
- Confirm all relations have matching foreign key indexes
